<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[820,1433,458,1426]" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[846,978,523,547]" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Description.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[1169,1245,524,548]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="4.9">4.9 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[1357,1431,524,548]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
(
<emphasis box="[829,842,557,580]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">n</emphasis>
=1). Epidermis whitish (
<figureCitation box="[1105,1186,556,580]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[156,187,1605,1627]" captionTargetBox="[158,764,206,1566]" captionTargetId="figure-625@11.[157,765,205,1567]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 8. Ototyphlonemertes (parmula) lei sp. nov., ICHUM 5365 (holotype). A, Entire body; B, composite photomicrograph of squeezed specimen; C, statolith; D, central stylet and basis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4583929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4583929/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
); cephalic furrow postcerebrally; tissues around brain slightly reddish; cirri present in both anterior and posterior ends of body. Foregut–intestine junction not distinct (
<figureCitation box="[1116,1192,654,678]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[156,187,1605,1627]" captionTargetBox="[158,764,206,1566]" captionTargetId="figure-625@11.[157,765,205,1567]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 8. Ototyphlonemertes (parmula) lei sp. nov., ICHUM 5365 (holotype). A, Entire body; B, composite photomicrograph of squeezed specimen; C, statolith; D, central stylet and basis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4583929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4583929/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
). Statolith polygranular (
<figureCitation box="[828,907,686,710]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[156,187,1605,1627]" captionTargetBox="[158,764,206,1566]" captionTargetId="figure-625@11.[157,765,205,1567]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 8. Ototyphlonemertes (parmula) lei sp. nov., ICHUM 5365 (holotype). A, Entire body; B, composite photomicrograph of squeezed specimen; C, statolith; D, central stylet and basis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4583929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4583929/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
), 
<quantity box="[929,996,686,711]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="9.3">9.3 µm</quantity>
in diameter (
<emphasis box="[1142,1155,687,710]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">n</emphasis>
=1), consisting of about 7 granules; statocyst 
<quantity box="[1024,1104,719,743]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.59" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="15.9">15.9 µm</quantity>
in diameter (
<emphasis box="[1260,1273,720,743]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">n</emphasis>
=1). Proboscis diaphragm short (
<figureCitation box="[1003,1078,751,775]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[156,187,1605,1627]" captionTargetBox="[158,764,206,1566]" captionTargetId="figure-625@11.[157,765,205,1567]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 8. Ototyphlonemertes (parmula) lei sp. nov., ICHUM 5365 (holotype). A, Entire body; B, composite photomicrograph of squeezed specimen; C, statolith; D, central stylet and basis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4583929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4583929/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
); two accessory stylet pouches, lateral to central-stylet basis, each containing 4 and 5 accessory stylets, all directing forward; central stylet (as well as accessory stylets) spiral (
<figureCitation box="[1052,1132,849,873]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[156,187,1605,1627]" captionTargetBox="[158,764,206,1566]" captionTargetId="figure-625@11.[157,765,205,1567]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 8. Ototyphlonemertes (parmula) lei sp. nov., ICHUM 5365 (holotype). A, Entire body; B, composite photomicrograph of squeezed specimen; C, statolith; D, central stylet and basis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4583929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4583929/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
), 
<quantity box="[1151,1232,849,873]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.47" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="54.7">54.7 µm</quantity>
long; basis 
<quantity box="[1352,1433,849,873]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.32" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="43.2">43.2 µm</quantity>
long, 8.0 µm wide (
<figureCitation box="[1017,1097,881,906]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[156,187,1605,1627]" captionTargetBox="[158,764,206,1566]" captionTargetId="figure-625@11.[157,765,205,1567]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 8. Ototyphlonemertes (parmula) lei sp. nov., ICHUM 5365 (holotype). A, Entire body; B, composite photomicrograph of squeezed specimen; C, statolith; D, central stylet and basis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4583929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4583929/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
), with each ridge twisting about 1.5 times; basis length/width ratio 5.4; middle chamber short; posterior chamber vesicular, without specialized anterior portion (
<figureCitation box="[959,1037,979,1003]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[156,187,1605,1627]" captionTargetBox="[158,764,206,1566]" captionTargetId="figure-625@11.[157,765,205,1567]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 8. Ototyphlonemertes (parmula) lei sp. nov., ICHUM 5365 (holotype). A, Entire body; B, composite photomicrograph of squeezed specimen; C, statolith; D, central stylet and basis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4583929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4583929/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
). Intestinal diverticula deep. Posterior adhesive plate with cells containing dark contents. Gonads found in posterior half of intestinal region, alternating more or less regularly with intestinal lateral diverticula.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="24" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[820,1433,458,1426]" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[846,985,1109,1133]" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Distribution.</emphasis>
So far known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[1303,1347,1110,1134]" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">type</typeStatus>
locality, the island of Dam Ngoai, 
<collectingCountry box="[1078,1168,1142,1166]" name="Vietnam" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="24" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[820,1433,458,1426]" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[846,965,1174,1198]" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is a noun in the genitive case, after Dr Doan Dung Le at the 
<collectingRegion box="[1188,1377,1207,1231]" country="Vietnam" name="Ho Chi Minh City" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Ho Chi Minh City</collectingRegion>
University of Food Industry, 
<collectingCountry box="[1083,1173,1239,1263]" name="Vietnam" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, who kindly coordinated HK’s sampling trip to Phu Quoc.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[820,1433,458,1426]" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[846,945,1304,1328]" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Remarks.</emphasis>
In the phylogenetic tree, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Diesing" authorityYear="1863" box="[1243,1431,1304,1328]" class="Enopla" family="Ototyphlonemertidae" genus="Ototyphlonemertes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monostilifera" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" phylum="Nemertea" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1243,1431,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Ototyphlonemertes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Correa" authorityYear="1950" box="[829,914,1337,1361]" class="Enopla" family="Ototyphlonemertidae" genus="Ototyphlonemertes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monostilifera" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" phylum="Nemertea" rank="species" species="parmula">
<emphasis box="[829,914,1337,1361]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">parmula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<emphasis box="[930,953,1337,1361]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">lei</emphasis>
sp. nov. appeared to be sister to the rest of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Correa" authorityYear="1950" box="[820,936,1369,1393]" class="Enopla" family="Ototyphlonemertidae" genus="Ototyphlonemertes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monostilifera" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" phylum="Nemertea" rank="species" species="parmula">
<emphasis box="[820,936,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">O. parmula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group (
<figureCitation box="[1098,1159,1369,1393]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[156,187,2023,2045]" captionTargetBox="[228,1359,206,1985]" captionTargetId="figure-7@3.[227,1360,205,1985]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Part of the phylogenetic tree resulting from the maximum-likelihood analysis of COI (ln L=−15264.650301), along with results of three species-delimitation analyses, ABGD, PTP, and TCS, as indicated by vertical bars. Numbers near nodes indicate maximum-likelihood bootstrap support value." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4583907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4583907/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), which was mostly represented by the Fila morpho-group of 
<bibRefCitation author="Leasi, F. &amp; Andrade, S. C. S. &amp; Norenburg, J." box="[1186,1366,1402,1426]" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" pagination="1381 - 1397" refId="ref10737" refString="Leasi, F., Andrade, S. C. S., and Norenburg, J. 2016. At least some meiofaunal species are not everywhere. Indication of geographic, ecological and geological barriers affecting the dispersion of species of Ototyphlonemertes (Nemertea, Hoplonemertea). Molecular Ecology 25: 1381 - 1397." type="journal article" year="2016">
Leasi 
<emphasis box="[1244,1293,1402,1426]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
